.TH "POWERKILL" "8" "October 11, 2025" "Powerkill User Manuals" ""
.SH NAME
powerkill \- unified process kill level processor
.SH SYNOPSIS
powerkill [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]PID\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Powerkill iterates over the process kill levels 1..65536 using all of
the named signal numbers from \f[CR]kill \-l \[rs]{1..64}\f[R] and
additionally for unamed signal numbers.
.PP
Useful in cases to save time where \f[CR]kill _PID_\f[R] does not
immedately resolve closing a process it deliberately overlooks
\f[CR]kill \-n 0 _PID_\f[R] that for example does not terminate
cpueater.py where powerkill \f[I]PID\f[R] does.
.IP
.EX
powerkill 1234
.EE
.PP
Iterates kill \-n {1..65536} 1234
.IP
.EX
powerkill \[ga]ps \-ae | grep _process name_ | awk \[aq]{print $1}\[aq]\[ga]
.EE
.PP
Iterates kill \-n {1..65536} \f[I]PID\f[R] of \f[I]process name\f[R]
.SH OPTIONS
powerkill takes one option and PID.
.TP
\-a, \-\-all
Iterates through all process kill levels
.TP
\-\-timer
Start a process timer.
.TP
\-h, \-\-help
Show usage message.
